    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Power Cylinders - Engine Run-in
        (Break-in) Procedure
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Engine Run-in (Break-in) Procedure</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, shift transmission to park or neutral, set parking brake,
                        and block wheels before doing diagnostic or service procedures.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <para>If new pistons, piston rings, or cylinder sleeves have been installed, use the following engine run-in
                procedure:
            </para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="runin" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Start engine and run at low idle with no load for 5 minutes. Check for leaks in the
                    cooling, oil, fuel, and air induction systems.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the turbocharger for all of the following conditions:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Unusual noise</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Oil leaks</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Air leaks</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Excessive exhaust smoke</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Excessive vibration</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Loose mounting</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn engine off and correct any of these conditions to prevent engine or turbocharger
                    damage.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Start engine and drive vehicle (unloaded) for 25 minutes in city mode, then drive
                    vehicle (unloaded) for an additional 15 minutes in highway mode.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Return to idle and check for leaks.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
